<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1441,194,1850]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,330,1602,1626]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Larva.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[335,497,1602,1626]" captionStart="Figures 132–133" captionStartId="62.[192,288,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,634,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-75@62.[192,1440,620,1800]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="Figures 132–133. Purenleon abruptus Stange, larva. 132) dorsal view; 133) ventral view. Figures 134–135. Purenleon albovaria (Banks), larva. 134) dorsal view; 135) ventral view. Figures 136–139. Purenleon connexus (Banks), larva. 136) dorsal view, California, USA; 137) dorsal view, Colima, Mexico; 138) ventral view, California, USA; 139) ventral view of head, Colima, Mexico." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5179584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5179584/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 132–133</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,655,1601,1625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Coloration</emphasis>
: mandible pale brown; ventral head capsule with six dark brown spots, largest submedial behind lateral tentorial suture, two close marks near middle, two submedial marks in posterior one-fifth. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[536,693,1665,1689]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Chaetotaxy</emphasis>
: dorsal surface of head capsule with prominent sublateral row of large dolichasters posterior to lateral tentorial suture (as in 
<figureCitation box="[975,1079,1697,1722]" captionStart="Figures 148–151" captionStartId="64.[192,288,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,381,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-68@64.[192,1440,379,1825]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Figures 148–151. Purenleon cavei Miller and Stange, larva. 148) dorsal view; 149) ventral view; 150) dorsal view of head; 151) ventral view of head. Figures 152–155. Purenleon clavatus (Navás), larva. 152) dorsal view; 153) ventral view; 154) dorsal view of head; 155) ventral view of head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5179588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5179588/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
); dorsal abdominal segments IV–VII with bead-like setae; ventral head capsule with bead-like setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1211,1729,1753]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Structure</emphasis>
: mandible at least as long as length of ventral head capsule measured at center, distance between tooth 1 and 3 a little longer than that between tooth 1 and base of mandible; abdominal spiracles easily visible, but shorter than or equal to basal width.
</paragraph>
